'''Sir Gerald Clayton Beadle''' was a President of the [[British Broadcasting Corporation]]  (BBC).

He joined the BBC in 1923, moving to their television team in 1936.<ref name="Pryor">{{cite web|url=http://texasarchive.org/library/index.php?title=Cactus_Pryor_Interviews_Sir_Gerald_Beadle_%281961%29|title=Cactus Pryor Interviews Sir Gerald Beadle|date=November 23, 1961|work=Cactus Pryor Show|accessdate=28 July 2014}}</ref> He was instrumental in establishing the BBC's [[Television Centre]], in London.

He was knighted in December 1960.<ref name="Pryor" />

He appeared as a "castaway" on the [[BBC Radio]] programme ''[[Desert Island Discs]]'' on 30 October 1961.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/features/desert-island-discs/castaway/2daa64fe#p009y6d1 |title=Desert Island Discs - Castaway : Sir Gerald Beadle |work=[[BBC Online]] |publisher=BBC |accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref>

